 (I-A)^{-1} = \sum_{n=0}^{\infty}A^n 
\implies  ||(I-A)^{-1}|| = ||\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}A^n||\leq \sum_{n=0}^{\infty}||A^n||\leq \sum_{n=0}^{\infty}||A||^n=\frac{1}{1-||A||}  
 \implies ||(I-A)^{-1}|| \leq \frac{1}{1-||A||}. 
